<% content_for :title, "Support — RoomScope" %>
<% content_for :head do %>
  <meta name="description" content="Get support for RoomScope, including Solo Pro subscriptions, PDF reports, custom checklists, and site survey workflows.">
<% end %>

<main class="legal-page">
  <nav class="site-nav legal-nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
    <a class="brand-mark" href="/" aria-label="RoomScope home">
      <span class="brand-icon">RS</span>
      <span>RoomScope</span>
    </a>
    <a class="nav-cta" href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
  </nav>

  <article class="legal-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Help & contact</p>
    <h1>RoomScope Support</h1>
    <p>
      Need help with RoomScope, Solo Pro, custom checklists, or PDF reports? Send a note with your
      device model, iOS version, and a short description of what happened.
    </p>

    <div class="support-callout">
      <strong>Email support</strong>
      <a href="mailto:support@getroomscope.com">support@getroomscope.com</a>
    </div>

    <h2>Common support topics</h2>
    <ul class="legal-list">
      <li>Getting started with room-by-room site surveys.</li>
      <li>Using standard system templates for AV, security, lighting, networking, and smart home projects.</li>
      <li>Unlocking Solo Pro features such as custom system categories and PDF report export.</li>
      <li>Restoring a Solo Pro subscription purchased through Apple.</li>
      <li>Exporting or sharing a project report PDF.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Solo Pro subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      Solo Pro purchases and renewals are handled by Apple through your App Store account. In the app,
      use Restore Purchases if you already subscribed and paid features are not active.
    </p>

    <h2>Response time</h2>
    <p>
      RoomScope is currently operated by a small independent developer. We try to respond to support
      requests as quickly as practical.
    </p>
  </article>
</main>
